In Minnesota elections, as in every state, there are rules. These are referred to, sometimes, as election laws. They may be referred to as codes or statutes, too. The statutes aren’t the only rules: the statutes have been written to give the Minnesota Secretary of State the option to add rules or to clarify the statutes. (I think this is unnecessary.)

